{title: Freeborn Man}
{artist: Glen Campbell}
{composer: Written by Keith Allison and Mark Lindsay}

[C]I was born in southland twenty some odd years ago
I ran away for the first time when I was four years [C7]old
I'm a freeborn [F]man   my home is on [C]my back
I know [G7]every inch of highway [F]every foot of
Back road every mile of railroad [C]track
I got a gal Cincinnati I got a woman in San Antone
I've always loved the girl next door but any place is [C7]home
Repeat #2


Got me a worn out guitar I carry in an old coal sack
I've hocked it bout two hundred times but I always get it [C7]back
Repeat #2

You may not like my appearance may not like my song
May not like the way I talk but you'll like me when I'm [C7]gone
Repeat #2  x2